24/08/2003
ATHENS, Greece -- On Saturday (23 August), Prime Minister Costas Simitis visited the site of the Ancient Olympia Old Museum, which is to be renovated and transformed into a future Olympic Games museum. Simitis also visited the construction site of the new Ancient Olympia highway, part of the national Pyrgos-Olympia-Vytina-Tripoli motorway that is being built especially for next year's Games. (ANA - 23/08/03)
